                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d650">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/17898</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Special Representative <persName type="from"
                            >Rodgers</persName> to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Mexico City</hi>
                        </placeName>, [<date
                            ana="#date_undated-inferred-from-document-content-and-sibling-dates"
                            calendar="gregorian" notAfter="1916-04-17T23:50:00-05:00"
                            notBefore="1916-04-07T17:00:00-07:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">undated</hi>
                        </date>
                        <hi rend="italic">; received April 17, 1916, 11.50 p.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>18. Secretary of State for Foreign Affairs requests me to state for General
                    Carranza that while he has received oral communication in relation to matter of
                    withdrawal American troops from Mexico presented in note of <hi rend="italic">de
                        facto</hi> Government 12th instant, he desires formal reply in text of
                    Department Washington.</p>
                <p>Evidently there will be no further discussion until such formal note presented.
                    General Carranza undoubtedly desires formal note in order to publish same if it
                    is necessary.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Rodgers</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
